    "# Task 4: Context-Aware Chatbot Using LangChain & RAG\n",
    "\n",
    "**Internship:** DevelopersHub Corporation – AI/ML Engineering (Advanced)\n",
    "\n",
    "## Problem Statement & Objective\n",
    "Build a conversational chatbot that:\n",
    "1. **Remembers conversation history** (context memory)\n",
    "2. **Retrieves relevant information** from a vectorised document store (RAG)\n",
    "3. **Grounds answers** in the provided knowledge base, reducing hallucinations\n",
    "4. Is deployed via an interactive **Streamlit** interface\n",
    "\n",
    "## Methodology\n",
    "1. Load and chunk a custom knowledge corpus\n",
    "2. Embed chunks with a sentence transformer\n",
    "3. Store in a FAISS vector database\n",
    "4. Build a LangChain ConversationalRetrievalChain with memory\n",
    "5. Deploy with Streamlit"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "!pip install langchain langchain-community langchain-openai \\\n",
    "             faiss-cpu sentence-transformers streamlit \\\n",
    "             openai tiktoken -q"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Imports ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "import os\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "from langchain.text_splitter import RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter\n",
    "from langchain_community.vectorstores import FAISS\n",
    "from langchain_community.embeddings import HuggingFaceEmbeddings\n",
    "from langchain.memory import ConversationBufferMemory\n",
    "from langchain.chains import ConversationalRetrievalChain\n",
    "from langchain_openai import ChatOpenAI\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Imports successful.\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nNOTE: Set your OPENAI_API_KEY environment variable before running the chain.\")\n",
    "print(\"  export OPENAI_API_KEY='sk-...'\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nAlternative: Use HuggingFace models (see 'Open-Source LLM Alternative' section)\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Knowledge Base Construction"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Sample Knowledge Base ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "# Replace with any real corpus: Wikipedia pages, PDFs, internal docs, etc.\n",
    "CORPUS = \"\"\"\n",
    "## Machine Learning Overview\n",
    "Machine learning (ML) is a branch of artificial intelligence that enables systems to learn\n",
    "and improve from experience without being explicitly programmed. ML focuses on developing\n",
    "computer programs that can access data and use it to learn for themselves.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Types of Machine Learning\n",
    "Supervised learning involves training a model on labelled data. Common algorithms include\n",
    "linear regression, logistic regression, decision trees, random forests, and neural networks.\n",
    "The goal is to learn a mapping from input features to output labels.\n",
    "\n",
    "Unsupervised learning works with unlabelled data to discover hidden patterns. Clustering\n",
    "(K-Means, DBSCAN), dimensionality reduction (PCA, t-SNE), and generative models belong\n",
    "to this category.\n",
    "\n",
    "Reinforcement learning trains agents to make decisions by rewarding desired behaviours.\n",
    "Deep Q-Networks (DQN) and Proximal Policy Optimisation (PPO) are popular algorithms.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Neural Networks and Deep Learning\n",
    "A neural network is a computational model inspired by the human brain, consisting of\n",
    "interconnected layers of neurons. Deep learning refers to neural networks with many layers.\n",
    "Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) excel at image recognition tasks. Recurrent Neural\n",
    "Networks (RNNs) and LSTMs handle sequential data. Transformers, introduced in 2017,\n",
    "revolutionised NLP and are now used across domains.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Transfer Learning\n",
    "Transfer learning leverages pre-trained models (e.g., BERT, GPT, ResNet) and fine-tunes\n",
    "them on domain-specific data. This dramatically reduces training time and data requirements.\n",
    "Hugging Face provides thousands of pre-trained models via its Model Hub.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Evaluation Metrics\n",
    "Classification tasks use accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score. Regression tasks use\n",
    "MAE (Mean Absolute Error), MSE (Mean Squared Error), and RMSE. For ranking tasks,\n",
    "NDCG and MAP are common. ROC-AUC measures binary classifier discrimination ability.\n",
    "\n",
    "## RAG: Retrieval-Augmented Generation\n",
    "RAG combines a retrieval system with a generative model. Given a query, relevant documents\n",
    "are retrieved from a vector database and provided as context to the LLM. This grounds\n",
    "responses in factual information and reduces hallucinations. LangChain and LlamaIndex are\n",
    "popular frameworks for building RAG applications.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Vector Databases\n",
    "Vector databases store high-dimensional embeddings and enable semantic similarity search.\n",
    "Popular options include FAISS (Facebook AI), Pinecone, Chroma, Weaviate, and Qdrant.\n",
    "Embeddings are generated by models like sentence-transformers or OpenAI embeddings.\n",
    "\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Save as text files (simulating a real document corpus) ─────────────────────\n",
    "Path(\"knowledge_base\").mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n",
    "with open(\"knowledge_base/ml_overview.txt\", \"w\") as f:\n",
    "    f.write(CORPUS)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Knowledge base saved.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Document Chunking & Vectorisation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from langchain_community.document_loaders import TextLoader, DirectoryLoader\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load documents\n",
    "loader = DirectoryLoader(\"knowledge_base\", glob=\"*.txt\", loader_cls=TextLoader)\n",
    "documents = loader.load()\n",
    "print(f\"Loaded {len(documents)} document(s)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Chunk documents with overlap to preserve context\n",
    "splitter = RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter(\n",
    "    chunk_size=500,\n",
    "    chunk_overlap=50,\n",
    "    separators=[\"\\n\\n\", \"\\n\", \". \", \" \"],\n",
    ")\n",
    "chunks = splitter.split_documents(documents)\n",
    "print(f\"Split into {len(chunks)} chunks\")\n",
    "print(f\"Sample chunk:\\n{chunks[0].page_content[:200]}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Embed with a free HuggingFace sentence-transformer ────────────────────────\n",
    "print(\"Loading embedding model (all-MiniLM-L6-v2)…\")\n",
    "embeddings = HuggingFaceEmbeddings(\n",
    "    model_name=\"all-MiniLM-L6-v2\",\n",
    "    model_kwargs={\"device\": \"cpu\"},\n",
    "    encode_kwargs={\"normalize_embeddings\": True},\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Build FAISS vector store\n",
    "print(\"Building FAISS vector store…\")\n",
    "vectorstore = FAISS.from_documents(chunks, embeddings)\n",
    "vectorstore.save_local(\"faiss_index\")\n",
    "print(f\"Vector store saved. Total vectors: {vectorstore.index.ntotal}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. RAG Chain with Conversation Memory"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def build_rag_chain(openai_api_key: str = None):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Build a ConversationalRetrievalChain.\n",
    "    If no OpenAI key is provided, falls back to a HuggingFace inference endpoint.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    # Load vector store\n",
    "    vs = FAISS.load_local(\"faiss_index\", embeddings, allow_dangerous_deserialization=True)\n",
    "    retriever = vs.as_retriever(search_kwargs={\"k\": 3})\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Conversation memory\n",
    "    memory = ConversationBufferMemory(\n",
    "        memory_key=\"chat_history\",\n",
    "        return_messages=True,\n",
    "        output_key=\"answer\",\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    if openai_api_key:\n",
    "        llm = ChatOpenAI(\n",
    "            model=\"gpt-3.5-turbo\",\n",
    "            temperature=0.2,\n",
    "            openai_api_key=openai_api_key,\n",
    "        )\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        # ── Open-Source Alternative: HuggingFace TGI / local Llama ──────────────\n",
    "        from langchain_community.llms import HuggingFacePipeline\n",
    "        from transformers import pipeline as hf_pipeline\n",
    "        pipe = hf_pipeline(\n",
    "            \"text-generation\",\n",
    "            model=\"facebook/opt-125m\",  # swap for Mistral-7B, Llama-3 etc.\n",
    "            max_new_tokens=256,\n",
    "            do_sample=False,\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        llm = HuggingFacePipeline(pipeline=pipe)\n",
    "\n",
    "    chain = ConversationalRetrievalChain.from_llm(\n",
    "        llm=llm,\n",
    "        retriever=retriever,\n",
    "        memory=memory,\n",
    "        return_source_documents=True,\n",
    "        verbose=False,\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    return chain\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"RAG chain builder defined.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
